h backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def maxScore(self, s: str) -> int:\n        max_score = 0\n        # Iterate through possible split points\n        for i in range(1, len(s)):\n            left = s[:i]\n            right = s[i:]\n            score = left.count('0') + right.count('1')\n            max_score = max(max_score, score)\n        return max_score\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through all possible ways to split the string into two non-empty substrings, calculates the score for each split, and keeps track of the maximum score encountered. The constraints are small enough (with a maximum string length of 500) that this approach will perform efficiently.", "estimated_date": 1587859200000}